value.title: Biden targets assault weapons, but handguns used more often in mass shootings
value.excerpt: According to Statistica, “handguns are involved in about 78% of mass shootings” in the United States between 1985 and 2021, making them the most common weapon used in these tragedies.

value.excerpt: President Biden is set to hold his first formal press conference on Thursday, and former White House press secretary Kayleigh McEnany told "Hannity" that it’s imperative that he be pressed on the situation at the southern border.

value.excerpt: "The View" co-host Meghan McCain issued an apology on Monday after she was called out by "Last Week Tonight" host John Oliver for comments she made about rhetoric tying the coronavirus outbreak to China.

value.title: Biden regularly consults with Barack Obama on a 'range of issues', Psaki says
value.excerpt: White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki on Monday said that President Biden maintains “regular” communication with President Barack Obama on a number of issues.

value.title: Mo Brooks spotlights support for Trump as he launches Alabama Senate bid
value.excerpt: Rep. Mo Brooks is showcasing his support for former President Trump as he jumps into the race to succeed retiring longtime Republican Sen. Richard Shelby of Alabama.

value.title: Kamala Harris laughs after reporter asks if she plans to visit border: 'Not today!'
value.excerpt: While taking questions from reporters outside of Air Force One, Harris was asked if she had "plans to visit" to the Southern border as the immigration crisis continues to develop.

value.excerpt: MSNBC anchor Brian Williams touted a new ad released by the disgraced Lincoln Project last week that tried to tie former President Donald Trump's rhetoric about the coronavirus to the March 16 Atlanta spa shootings.

value.title: Biden HHS to turn San Diego Convention Center into migrant shelter
value.excerpt: The Biden Administration is turning the San Diego Convention Center into a temporary shelter to support unaccompanied children seeking asylum in the United States.

value.excerpt: Biden world sang the praises of Democratic strategist Adrienne Elrod on Sunday after a glowing profile on her work with Biden's team.

value.excerpt: House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy hired one of former President Trump's top staffers to lead his political operation, a source familiar with the hire told Fox News.

value.title: Trump returning to social media with 'his own platform' in 2-3 months: adviser
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump will be back on social media in the near future with his own service, according to one of his senior advisers.

value.title: Biden response to border crisis 'isn't incompetence', but 'is by design', Tom Homan tells Mark Levin
value.excerpt: President Biden "sold out this country to the progressive left to win an election," former Immigration and Customs Enforcement Acting Director Tom Homan told "Life, Liberty & Levin" in an interview airing Sunday.

value.title: Trump boosts Julia Letlow in Louisiana House race to succeed her late husband
value.excerpt: Former President Trump urged his supporters to back Julia Letlow Saturday in the special election House race in Louisana to succeed her late husband, Luke, who died after contracting coronavirus.

value.title: Harris, in apparent swipe at Trump, says people ‘with the biggest pulpits’ spewed hate toward Asian Americans
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris, speaking in Atlanta in the wake of this week's mass shooting, said that people in power had been "scapegoating Asian Americans,” an apparent reference to Donald Trump.

value.title: Baltimore prosecutor Marilyn Mosby, once championed by VP Harris, now target of federal investigation
value.excerpt: State's Attorney for Baltimore Marilyn Mosby, whose career was boosted by Vice President Kamala Harris, is now facing a federal investigation with a wide breadth of subpoenas.

value.title: Biden White House says it's ready to have 'frank conversation' with China
value.excerpt: The White House said the Biden administration is ready to have a "frank conversation" with China and is negotiating from a position of "strength," as officials hold tense bilateral talks with Beijing.

value.title: Kevin McCarthy on 'Fox & Friends': Biden border crisis now becoming 'human tragedy'
value.excerpt: The issues on the border go beyond a crisis to a "human tragedy," House Minority Leader Kevin McCarthy, R-Calif., said on Friday, reacting to the Biden administration denying media access to migrant facilities.

value.title: Florida ex-Sen. Bill Nelson to be tapped by Biden for NASA administrator
value.excerpt: President Biden is expected to tap former Democratic Sen. Bill Nelson to lead NASA -- a move that could come as early as Friday, multiple current and former NASA officials told Fox News.

value.title: Texas wax museum moves Trump statue because visitors kept hitting it: report
value.excerpt: The owner of Louis Tussaud’s Waxworks in San Antonio said the museum removed a statue of former President Trump because too many visitors punched and scratched the figure, a report said.

value.title: Kellyanne Conway, Michael Wolff, Jonathan Karl among those reportedly writing post-White House Trump books
value.excerpt: The era of explosive tell-all books about the Trump presidency is apparently not over, even though the presidency itself has ended.

value.title: Biden touts fight against 'climate crisis' while refusing to call border ‘crisis’
value.excerpt: In a tweet posted Thursday, the president lauded the swearing-in of his new Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) Administrator Michael Regan and boasted how his new environment czar will fight the “climate crisis.”

value.title: Giroir accuses Biden of playing 'fast and loose' with COVID science, taking credit for Operation Warp Speed
value.excerpt: President Biden is somehow able to "stand up and completely rewrite history and go fast and loose with the science and the data," former HHS Assistant Secretary Brett Giroir told "The Story" Thursday.

value.title: Biden calls his second-in-command 'President Harris'
value.excerpt: President Biden appeared to misspeak in a speech Thursday offering updates on an update on vaccination progress in the U.S., referring to his vice president as “President Harris.”

value.title: Vanita Gupta could be Biden's 'most dangerous' DOJ pick, GOP senator argues, while Dem leader decries 'smears'
value.excerpt: The Senate Judiciary Committee met Wednesday to discuss President Biden's nominations of Lisa Monaco to be the next deputy attorney general and Vanita Gupta as associate attorney general.

value.excerpt: The Biden administration continues to ignore the crisis at the border while the migrant surge worsens, Rep. Troy Nehls told "Fox & Friends."'

value.title: Biden 'pandering to coastal elite friends' with Keystone pipeline shutdown: Montana AG
value.excerpt: Montana Attorney General Austin Knudsen said Thursday that President Biden's shutdown of the Keystone pipeline is really just "pandering to his coastal elite friends."
